Class GameEvent

java.lang.Object
com.comp3607.logger.GameEvent
public class GameEvent extends Object
Represents an event that occurs during the game, capturing relevant details for logging purposes

  • Constructor Details

    • GameEvent

      public GameEvent(String caseId, String playerName, String activity, LocalDateTime timestamp, Question question, String answerGiven, String result, int scoreAfter)
      Creates a GameEvent object containing all of the details of an event occurring in the game
      Parameters:
      caseId - the id of the event
      playerName - the name of the player who triggered the event
      activity - the activity which takes place upon trigger
      timestamp - the time at which the event occurred
      question - the question which the event was triggered upon
      answerGiven - the answer given to the question selected
      result - the resolution of the answer checked against the question
      scoreAfter - the updated score after the event resolves
